The paper deals with coded caching, which is a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also heavily relies on graph theory and combinatorics, specifically bipartite graphs and clique covers, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (discrete mathematics) or cs.CC (computational complexity). The paper also discusses the transmission scheme for satisfying user demands, which could fall under cs.NI (networking and internet architecture) or cs.SI (social and information networks).
